Cell[TextData[{
 "Under Newton\[CloseCurlyQuote]s second law of motion, the state of a \
classical system (particle) evolves over time being governed by the \
celebrated equation of motion, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"F", "=", 
    RowBox[{"m", " ", "a"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e9a6a36e-71cd-42be-93a5-915ad81fd25a"],
 "., where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["F", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7b21d552-a2ed-47fe-9d08-93f5a307e703"],
 " is the force on the system, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["m", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2a5c9f4f-82e4-4e38-92c8-194ee40722a0"],
 " is the mass of the system, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["a", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "21b760fc-341f-431e-b5ca-b8cfe2ee483f"],
 " is the acceleration of the system. In quantum mechanics, Newton\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s equation of motion is replaced with \
Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger\[CloseCurlyQuote]s."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->131888160,ExpressionUUID->"1f2175e5-2cd3-4c50-b060-52709513dea8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See also Section 1.2 of the ",
