Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Unitary Dynamics", "TechNoteSection",
 CellTags->"Section11",
 CellID->903787946,ExpressionUUID->"cf11b2ea-f641-4151-895c-2b0db44c8791"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Postulate 2",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The time evolution of the state |\[Psi]\:27e9 of a closed quantum system \
is governed by the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->812173191,ExpressionUUID->"c9fa51ab-2671-448e-9573-6a534cd1bfd2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[HBar]", " ", 
     FractionBox["d", 
      RowBox[{"d", " ", "t"}]], 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
      "Ket"]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"H", 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1ebee2a9-8048-45f9-ae4f-23a3347fe857"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->788760805,ExpressionUUID->"a2a686e0-846f-4c23-8d0f-1c4130944bfd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[HBar]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "98bc1705-8504-4dad-b1e1-6e64b990578b"],
 " is the Planck constant and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["H", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3de7018c-a72a-4113-9e1a-921cc205fe71"],
 " is the Hamiltonian of the system."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->286296704,ExpressionUUID->"5765f0dc-143b-4927-a0e1-68778823fe63"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tThroughout the tutorial document, we use a unit system where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d7da8084-20d6-46f3-b362-29e70376f40e"],
 ". In such a unit system, energy and frequency have the same dimension, the \
inverse of the dimension of time. The Hamiltonian is a Hermitian operator \
physically describing the energy of the system. In general, it is difficult \
to find the precise Hamiltonian for a particular system. In most cases, a \
model Hamiltonian is constructed and tested against experimental \
observations. If desired, it is corrected by changing the existing terms or \
including additional terms, and testing again."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1425334848,ExpressionUUID->"08f3e299-103d-473d-978b-22540f17f6ce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tPostulate 2 expresses the time evolution in terms of a differential \
equation. An equivalent way is to describe it with a unitary transformation. \
Suppose that the system is initially in a state |\[Psi](0)\:27e9, then the \
state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", "t", ")"}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "916aad9d-d7e9-4730-8357-03945b3ef3df"],
 " at later time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"t", ">", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8a880b3f-fb57-46e0-85b1-40715f132188"],
 " is related to the initial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", "0", ")"}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b049885c-57d4-4a8e-9675-52d07cacb41d"],
 " by a unitary operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"U", 
    RowBox[{"(", "t", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5e343022-a564-46f8-899d-4ce1099731dd"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->422708051,ExpressionUUID->"39fd3b82-fe9d-4892-84e9-f4efb99d9e2f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", "t", ")"}]},
     "Ket"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"U", "(", "t", ")"}], 
     TemplateBox[{
       RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", "0", ")"}]},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c3e3a069-5737-4926-8b9f-a0a074850cda"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->578308881,ExpressionUUID->"4d0f8dc9-4591-44dc-884b-992452b85c02"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The unitary operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"U", 
    RowBox[{"(", "t", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7a7a185e-216f-46a2-8a65-3394bbe3eff3"],
 " is called the ",
 StyleBox["time-evolution operator",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->126376645,ExpressionUUID->"dbf8e916-6837-44e0-9311-497eb3e4a0ea"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tWhen the Hamiltonian ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["H", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fc64c808-fa15-4165-88ef-aa39ec382c29"],
 " of the system is independent of time, the time-evolution operator is given \
by (recalling that we have put ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "adf1c786-4084-4545-8ac2-5911413f7f1d"],
 ")"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->971068552,ExpressionUUID->"394076d5-7566-406c-8fdc-5850450c5940"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"U", "(", "t", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"exp", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "t", " ", "H"}], ")"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"cce9b6a5-dcda-4637-8d3d-cc7ba259b5f7"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->150945632,ExpressionUUID->"40796da1-f0c9-451f-b34b-0cd247893d97"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The best way to evaluate the exponential function of a normal operator is \
to use its spectral decomposition. With the eigenstates ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"E"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "839c36a4-0290-4beb-a57d-0b29837e7bbc"],
 " and corresponding eigenvalues ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["E", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f618426e-e317-41fb-a9e4-ffab49eed532"],
 " of Hamiltonian ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["H", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ea63fbad-01c0-4278-959b-a9c82be2c4a7"],
 ", the Hamiltonian itself reads as"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->765049917,ExpressionUUID->"f3e93ba3-4428-4b2a-b1da-5ee23a0674f9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "E"], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"E"},
       "Ket"], "E", 
      TemplateBox[{"E"},
       "Bra"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "67c7c7ea-c95a-4ff2-b998-59813eec0d99"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1209360430,ExpressionUUID->"0d2412cd-af4a-432a-8d4f-78c0a993cb2f"],

Cell["Hence, its exponential function is given by", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1935511802,ExpressionUUID->"41ae37d6-36cb-487b-8403-df492dbe6465"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"exp", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "t", " ", "H"}], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "E"], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"E"},
       "Ket"], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "t", " ", "E"}]], 
      TemplateBox[{"E"},
       "Bra"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "38c6fbc6-026d-49e2-b732-faed52f96f13"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->64571458,ExpressionUUID->"71662d35-4581-4095-99e0-53d9f9a839f7"],

Cell["\<\
\tIn general, and especially when the system is driven externally to actively \
process quantum information, for example, the Hamiltonian depends on time. In \
this case, the relation between the time-evolution operator and the \
Hamiltonian is more complicated, and this will be discussed later.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->773252871,ExpressionUUID->"cf8ef71b-de21-41b3-a3aa-c094ade789ac"],

