    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Under Newton's second law of motion, the state of a classical system \
(particle) evolves over time being governed by the celebrated equation of \
motion, F=m a., where F is the force on the system, m is the mass of the \
system, and a is the acceleration of the system. In quantum mechanics, \
Newton's equation of motion is replaced with Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger's. See \
also Section 1.2 of the Quantum Workbook (2022). Postulate 2. The time \
evolution of the state |\\[Psi]\:27e9 of a closed quantum system is governed \
by the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {},
     "title" -> "Time Evolution", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> 
    "", "windowtitle" -> "Time Evolution", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
